![173.jpg](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/1618258087296-4Z8B91TJM4QOV0GMEOWQ/173.jpg)

With the destruction of The Darkest Knight at the end of Dark Knights Death Metal, the DC Universe looks forward to a familiar but also strange future. A future where Gotham is ruled by a militant force led by The Magistrate, Jon Kent is the savior of Metropolis and Diana faces off against a faceless foe at the end of time. Could this be a sign of things to come? What does this future say about what happens to these iconic characters? We talk all that in more at this glimpse into the "Future State" of DC Comics.**Please** leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our [merchandise](http://www.teepublic.com/user/comicbookclique)! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by [**ComicBookClique.com**](../episode/update/id/Comicbokclique.com), the home for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.  
  
